BR_text.BRsummary: Bug: Polygon must have at least 3 points
BR_text.BRdescription:
I am using cvat.org to test out the service. I used the MaskRCNN feature to annotate a video. After completion, I went into the job and found that I could not open it. I get this error in the console:
 cvat-app.tsx:192 Error: Polygon must have at least 3 points, but got 2
 I also see the same error in the window:
 Error: Polygon must have at least 3 points, but got 2
 However, I can open it in the Old UI no problem. This seems like a bug.

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/cinjon>@cinjon</denchmark-link>

comments_8.comment_text:
<denchmark-link:https://github.com/zhiltsov-max>@zhiltsov-max</denchmark-link>
  we looked at MaskRCNN output of two videos. It turns out those polygons with 4 values can be removed. If you look at those values both points are same.
 Take a look at this example:
 <denchmark-code>point 4 [523.0, 338.5, 523.0, 338.5]
 point 4 [268.0, 340.5, 268.0, 340.5]
 point 4 [208.0, 324.5, 208.0, 324.5]
 point 4 [1137.0, 246.5, 1137.0, 246.5]
 point 4 [269.0, 280.5, 269.0, 280.5]
 </denchmark-code>
 
 I also looked at some points with 4 values in the result that attached above. Same thing.
 I think we can just filter out those polygons in auto_segmentation/views.py. I understand we will be having lambda functions. But in the interim, this maybe the solution. We can send a PR if you want.
